{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_47","type":"agent_message","text":"I’m narrowing the runtime behavior to one place: `Reflect.lookup*()` loads a class by name and decides discoverability entirely via `Class.getAnnotation(EnableReflectiveInstantiation.class)` plus constructor/module inspection. That means the metadata fix is almost certainly about preserving reflective query access on the annotated test classes and module singleton fields, not broad library internals."}}
